summary: I hate to jump om the Brie Larson hating train but God it's painful to watch her interact with the rest of the cast. This is...
body: I hate to jump om the Brie Larson hating train but God it’s painful to watch her interact with the rest of the cast. This is coming from someone who actually thinks she’s a great actress. I genuinely liked Captain Marvel and thought she was phenomenal in Room, which is why I was confused by all the hate when she got cast. From every interview so far it’s like she says all the wrong things and has no sense of humour….at all. Or if she does her response to it is disproportionately serious to the statement made. The life of the interview is just sucked out. Maybe she’s just awkward…idk, I guess it’s not easy speaking as a public figure when you know the world is ready to hate, but she’s not exactly giving people any reason to warm up to her

Also, that cat. 👌

title: for the warrior girls.
body:
does your heart still beat?
most of the time, people don’t come from back from things like this
they can’t kill without blinking or drown without sinking
when they burn the world to a crisp, they can’t sleep at night

but you can sleep. you can dream.
you can slice open a throat and still manage to hope
that all of your decisions were justified by survival instincts
though, truth be told, you were always your best self
when you were facing another sharp edge of oblivion.

you shouldn’t be ashamed.
you’re the reason why they’re still breathing;
when they tell you you’re merciless, monstrous
tell them to remember they would’ve burned without you
tell them to remember you’ve killed for less.

you’ve hopped through the galaxy like the planets were trampolines
you’ve only just begun to understand that the universe is within you

and when you meet your end,
they will bury you beneath spring flowers and weep.
they will name civilizations after you,
so that you will never truly die.

question: top 5 favorite Captain Marvel moments?
answer:
oH MY GUY THAT’S A GOOD ONE

  • maria’s speech to carol after they learned the truth about carol and yon rogg, and the sun was setting and they were both emotional
  • when talos and other skrulls were poking through carol’s memories and (i made a post about this previously) how the scene smash cuts to a wide shot of carol walking out the opening hanger + the way moments just kept repeating or going backwards i thought it was an incredible way of showing the concept of looking through memories
  • every time carol smirked
  • when she finally pushed back and powered up to her full potential and kicked everyone’s ass to no doubt’s i’m just a girl and then fucking just smashing face first into alien ships like it was nothing..b O I
  • the last scene where she says goodbye to maria and monica and then looks down at earth with THE most fond and loving expression and just fucking flies at light speed away with the bombastic triumphant music catch me lying on the cold hard ground

+BONUS because i love this movie too much to stick to five

  • that montage of carol falling and then getting back up again because fuCk you oh man oh b o y
  • just literally every moment with goose and nick
  • nick and carol just becoming best friends/the buddy cop due i never knew i needed
  • the dinner scene at the end like hello? fOUND FAMILY??? bye
  • carol’s memories of maria and monica, that’s two moms and their kid content if i do say so myself
  • yon rogg getting his ass handed to him lmao
  • carol blowing the wisp of hair out of her face the SWAGGER
  • fury changing the protector initiative to the avenger initiative after carol’s call sign I’M VERKLEMPT WE WOULDN’T BE HERE WITHOUT HER SHE’S HIS HERO BYE
